==English==

===Adverb===
'''[[when]] [[pigs]] [[fly]]'''
# {{idiom}} [[never|Never]].

====Translations====
{{top}}
*Bulgarian: [[на куково лято]]
*Chinese: 除非太陽從西邊出來 / 除非太阳从西边出来<!--literally ''unless the Sun rises in the west'')-->
*Dutch: [[wanneer Pasen en Pinksteren op één dag vallen]] <!-- when Easter and Pentecost happen on the same day -->
*Dutch: [[met sint-juttemis]] <!-- originally "met sint-juttemis als de kalveren op het ijs dansen"--- at Saint Judith's (17 August) when the calves dance on the ice-->
*Finnish: [[kun lehmät lentävät]] <!--when cows fly-->
*French: [[quand les poules auront des dents]] <!--when chickens have teeth-->
*German: [[an Sankt Nimmerlein]]<!--at Saint Never ...-->, [[wenn Ostern und Pfingsten auf einen Tag fallen]] <!--when Easter and Pentecost happen on the same day-->
*Hindi: Sooraj pashchim se ugega <!--When the sun will rise in the West-->
*Hungarian: [[majd ha fagy]] <!--when it will be freezing-->
{{mid}}
*Malayalam: Kakka malannu parakkum <!--The crow will fly upside down; kakka = crow; malannu = upside down' parakkum = will fly)-->
*Russian: [[когда рак на горе свистнет]] (kogdá rak na goré svístnet)
*Swedish: [[när grisar flyger]] <!--when pigs fly-->
*Tagalog: [[sa pagputi ng uwak]] <!--when the crow turns white-->, [[sa pag-itim ng tagak]] <!--when the heron turns black-->
